{"name":"Giant Blood","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"szuK9RR2o1Fwvei3","changes":[{"key":"system.vitals.siz.value","value":"2","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.characteristics.str.value","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.characteristics.sta.value","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.mhpaBm1ti8C6zWaq","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals","characteristics","characteristics"],"subtype":["size","str","sta"],"option":[null,null,null]}},"name":"Giant","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"giant-blood","description":"The blood of the ancient race of giants flows in your veins. Though you are not as large as your ancestors, you are up to eight feet tall and can weigh as much as 500 pounds. Your Size is +2, so you take wounds in 7-point increments, rather than the normal 5 (see page 171). You also gain +1 to both Strength and Stamina. This bonus may raise your scores in those Characteristics as high as +6. You cannot take this Virtue and Large, Small Frame, or Dwarf."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751327,"modifiedTime":1696141995645,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jyD9OjMnXTZeke24","_id":"0F9O8x9jbRhCR1Zg","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Quiet Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[{"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Item.iu0yfAIc4gMftbyu","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"key":"system.stances.voice.quiet","value":"0","mode":5,"priority":null},{"mode":5,"key":"system.stances.voice.silent","value":"-5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["spellcasting","spellcasting"],"subtype":["voiceQuiet","voiceSilent"],"option":[null,null]}},"_id":"vl0XJpbxPSgOKgcN","transfer":true,"name":"Quiet Magic","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"quiet-magic","description":"You can cast spells using only a soft voice at no penalty, and at only a –5 penalty if you do not speak at all. You gain no benefits from using your voice normally but gain the normal benefit for using a booming voice. The range of Voice Range spells is determined normally, based on how loud your voice is. You may take this Virtue twice, and eliminate the penalty altogether."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751352,"modifiedTime":1696141995651,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"0WY13kLD6k24OU0V","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Mercurian Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":46,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"mercurian-magic","description":"Your magical lineage and traditions are from the Roman priests of Mercury, which predate the Order of Hermes, making you especially skilled with Ritual Magic and magic used 46 Spontaneous   magic   using   the   rules   for Ceremonial Casting (page 83)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751306,"modifiedTime":1696141995657,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"ryEkrZYbf9tQGIrO","_id":"0u4Tj1AuadcgHCUD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Tough","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"jBpkQbNivkfs0HwB","changes":[{"key":"system.bonuses.traits.soak","value":"3","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.btxtlpTLe24uYd1Z","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals"],"subtype":["soak"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Soak +3","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":49,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"tough","description":"You can take physical punishment better than most people. You get a +3 bonus on your Soak score."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751300,"modifiedTime":1696141995666,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"1DFTYivxLBhyiRqn","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Rapid Convalescence","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.3JztkrgfbkS7P8pD","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.traits.recovery","value":"3","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals"],"subtype":["recovery"],"option":[null]}},"_id":"qiikyTaJwFgMy13K","transfer":true,"name":"+3 to wound recovery","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"rapid-convalescence","description":"Your body can heal quickly. You get a +3 bonus on all rolls to recover from wounds."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751228,"modifiedTime":1696141995675,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"3JztkrgfbkS7P8pD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Redcap","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"Although you do not have The Gift and cannot work Hermetic magic, you are a full member of the Order of Hermes and of House Mercere (see page 12). There are Gifted members of House Mercere, but they do not take this Virtue, taking the Hermetic Magus Social Status (page 43) instead. You deliver messages for the Order, and you possess a number of enchanted devices to help you do this. A newly-Gauntleted Redcap has enchanted devices with fifty levels of effect, including modifications to the level due to factors such as the number of uses per day (see “Magical Enchantments,” page 95, for details). These levels are invariably split between two or more effects useful for delivering messages. New Redcaps are never given items capable of killing, wounding, or ensorcelling large numbers of mundanes; the risk of abuse bringing trouble on the Order is too great. These will be upgraded and replaced in return for good service, on average an extra two levels per year. You are trained in a similar manner to magi, and may take Academic, Arcane, and Martial Abilities during character generation. You have spent fifteen years as an apprentice, and gained a total of 300 experience points in those fifteen years. (See “Detailed Character Creation,” page 28.) In addition, you have the Well Traveled Virtue at no cost. When you start to age, a magus with a Lab Total of at least fifty will devise a Longevity Ritual (see page 101) for you free of charge, if you wish. If you make suitable contacts in the course of the saga, this ritual may be devised by a more powerful magus. You are supported by your covenant, so you cannot take the Wealthy Virtue or Poor Flaw. You may not take The Gift. You must spend two seasons per year delivering messages for the Order. Your other two seasons are, however, genuinely free, and you may do whatever you wish. This Virtue is available to male and female characters. Redcaps created some years past Gauntlet get improved enchanted devices, as described above, and, if applicable, a Longevity Ritual.","source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"redcap"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751317,"modifiedTime":1696141995684,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"5doiTaY9KQf8IBzO","_id":"3hA8d1zzdwwiqg1Q","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Luck","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":45,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"luck","description":"You perform well in situations where luck is more of a factor than skill or talent. You get +1 to +3 (storyguides discretion) on rolls in such situations, depending upon how much luck is involved. You do well at games of chance, but may be labeled a cheater if you play them too often."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751270,"modifiedTime":1696141995691,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"3uL6KGLslxkKVXLw","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Flawless Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"flawless-magic","description":"You automatically master every spell that you learn. All your spells start with a score of 1 42 in the corresponding Ability. You may choose a different special ability for every spell you have. Further, all experience points you put into Spell Mastery Abilities are doubled."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751310,"modifiedTime":1696141995697,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"ryEkrZYbf9tQGIrO","_id":"3wGfz0swU90h5KwO","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Mastered Spells","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":46,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"mastered-spells","description":"You have fifty experience points to spend on mastering spells that you know. (See page 86 for rules on mastering spells.) You may take this Virtue if you also have Flawless Magic, to give you more experience points to spend on mastering your spells. You may take this Virtue multiple times."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751349,"modifiedTime":1696141995702,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"450XFK8T0yupcoNd","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Enduring Constitution","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"Z8ApdwljNYpaTyMt","changes":[{"key":"system.fatigue.weary.number","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.fatigue.tired.number","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.fatigue.dazed.number","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.penalties.wounds.light","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"key":"system.penalties.wounds.medium","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null},{"mode":2,"key":"system.penalties.wounds.heavy","value":"1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.FT8b6iFv5uBOpbar","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["fatigue","fatigue","fatigue","wounds","wounds","wounds"],"subtype":["weary","tired","dazed","light","medium","heavy"],"option":[null,null,null,null,null,null]}},"name":"Enduring constitution","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"enduring-constitution","description":"You can withstand pain and fatigue. Decrease the penalties for reduced Fatigue levels by one point, and reduce your total penalty from wounds by one point (but not below zero). You also get +3 on rolls to resist pain."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751242,"modifiedTime":1696141995707,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"4FfB36d6REnmXwGU","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Gentle Gift","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"gentle-gift","description":"Unlike other magi, whose Magical nature disturbs normal people and animals, your Gift is subtle and quiet. You dont suffer the usual penalties when interacting with people and animals. GENTLEMAN/WOMAN Minor, Social Status You are a minor member (possibly illegitimate) of a noble family. You do not stand to inherit from your relatives, but are still treated as one of their own and may be addressed as “Lord” or “Lady.” You probably reside near the covenant with your relatives. Although you do not want for anything, you have no vast wealth of your own. You may occasionally ask your family to buy expensive equipment for you, but you will need a convincing rationale. You are expected to wait on your relations much of the time or you will lose the benefits of family (though you will keep your social standing if you can otherwise maintain your normal lifestyle). The Wealthy Virtue and Poor Flaw affect you normally. This Virtue is available to male and female characters."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751329,"modifiedTime":1696141995712,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"ryEkrZYbf9tQGIrO","_id":"4RPkNbijbzuTt5u0","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Book Learner","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"fsyqHHHCi18Tv8Sk","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.activities.reading","value":"3","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.qFhRohQtWHrT6Gm2","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["activities"],"subtype":["reading"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Book learner","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"book-learner","description":"You have a talent for comprehending the writings of others. When studying from books, treat them as if they were three Quality levels higher than they actually are."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751334,"modifiedTime":1696141995717,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"4XK6OFQHy9J9fZJY","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Death Prophecy","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"death-prophecy","description":"You have been blessed or cursed as to your fate. Someone (a magician, a faerie, or other supernatural creature) has put a condition on your death, and until the condition is met, you will not die, though you can be seriously injured. You heal normally, but cannot die as a result of wounds or old age. Unfortunately for you, fate or bad planning can bring about the conditions in unexpected ways. If, for instance, your death condition is to fear only boars, you should be wary of men bearing boars on their coats of arms or of inns named after boars, in addition to the purely mundane creature. This symbolism may not be obvious: a man known as a “pig” in his village might also count as a boar. The storyguide must keep the prophecy in mind and give fair warning of items related to the prophecy. This is a Major Virtue because the character knows he can get away with insane risks; sneaking his prophecy up on him is an unfair way of negating the value of the Virtue. Players may only take this Virtue with the agreement of the storyguide or troupe."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751217,"modifiedTime":1696141995721,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jyD9OjMnXTZeke24","_id":"4inZzlOt995Vbzga","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Ways Of The (land)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":50,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"ways-of-the-land","description":"You have a deep understanding of a type of terrain, feeling more natural and at home there than anywhere else. Examples include Ways of the Forest, Ways of the Mountain, Ways of the Steppe or Ways of the Town. You get a +3 bonus to all rolls, including combat, that directly involve that area and its inhabitants; mundane, magical, or faerie. In addition, you roll one fewer botch die than normal (which may mean you roll no botch dice) in rolls that pertain to your area of understanding. You are not normally molested by animals of the terrain, and though particularly vicious creatures may still attack you, at least they’ll accord you proper respect. (For Ways of the Town, this still applies to town animals, of which there are plenty in the medieval world, rather than people. The +3 bonus does apply to people.) You may choose this Virtue multiple times, for different types of terrain. 50"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751290,"modifiedTime":1696141995727,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jyD9OjMnXTZeke24","_id":"4zbMWi0N5gkGMSju","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Faerie Blood","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"ZRdm8YmVSxANqkIY","changes":[{"key":"system.realms.faeric.aligned","value":"true","mode":5,"priority":null},{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.traits.aging","value":"-1","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.G4m1LlEL19oB5CWx","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["realm","vitals"],"subtype":["faeric","aging"],"option":[null,null]}},"name":"Faerie blood (to configure)","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"Somewhere in your ancestry there is a faerie, and this relation gives you an intuitive grasp of the motivations and personalities of those mystical folk. Faeries are more comfortable around you than around other humans, and given time, may even forget the mortal blood in your veins. You are resistant to aging, and get –1 to all aging rolls. Type of Faerie Blood (pick one, or create a similar one): Dwarf Blood: You are descended from the master craftsmen of the fay, and get a +1 bonus to any total including a Craft Ability. Goblin Blood: Your ancestors were the sneaky inhabitants of the shadows underground, and you get a +1 bonus on all totals involving stealth. Satyr Blood: The satyrs are notoriously lecherous. \tYou \tget \ta \t+1 \tbonus \tto Communication and Presence totals when dealing with sexually compatible characters. Sidhe Blood: You are descended from one of the noble fay who rule the lands of Summer and sunlight. Because of the striking and unusual qualities of your nature add +1 to your Presence, but not to more than +3. Many mortals may consider you fascinating or alluring. Undine Blood: The undines are the faeries of the water, and you get a +2 bonus to any action taken underwater, which will partially offset any penalty applied. Characters with Faerie Blood can learn Faerie Lore at character generation.","source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"faerie-blood"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751243,"modifiedTime":1696141995731,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"54SGECTkYW5h24AX","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Affinity With (art)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[{"_id":"ux2586kvOboH4yBh","changes":[{"mode":0,"key":"","value":"","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.HYsMf6f4axdDNHjD","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["none"],"subtype":["none"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Affinity to be configured","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"affinity-with-art","description":"Your Study Totals for one Hermetic Art are increased by one half, rounded up. At character creation, any experience points you put into that Art are also increased by one half (rounded up), and you may exceed the normal recommended limits. You may take this Virtue twice, for two different Arts."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751250,"modifiedTime":1696141995736,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"5cG7sTSd7O8vvrMl","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Hermetic Prestige","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"hermetic-prestige","description":"Because of something in your back ground, other magi look up to you even if you haven’t earned their respect. Some envy you, and most will certainly expect more from you than from others. You gain a Reputation of level 3 within the Order."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751261,"modifiedTime":1696141995741,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"5pNq3S5Co6ptkwvf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Magical Memory","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":45,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"magical-memory","description":"Your memory has been developed to remember magical rather than mundane things. You need not keep laboratory texts (see page 101) of your creations to get the benefit of a Lab Text when reproducing them. If you have created an effect by following another magus’s lab text once, you may get the same benefit in future without needing to have the text available."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751236,"modifiedTime":1696141995745,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"609BvMocZ4JxUThl","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Puissant (art)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[{"_id":"X6B4YrvuSkRKZ2Mi","changes":[{"key":"","mode":2,"value":"","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.PhZnHgOvo4RxVTAq","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["none"],"subtype":["none"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Puissant art to be configured","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"puissant-art","description":"You add 3 to the value of one Art whenever you use it. This means all totals in which the score of the Art is part of the total. It does not apply to Study Totals. You may take this Virtue twice, for two different Arts. If a spell has requisites, include the bonus from Puissant Art with that Art when calculating which Art is higher. If the Puissant Art is higher, the bonus does not apply to the requisite."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751272,"modifiedTime":1696141995750,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"8JZWyVPJ13oVgB83","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Study Bonus","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":49,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"study-bonus","description":"When given the opportunity to study an Art from books or raw vis in the presence of the Form or Technique, your surroundings give you new insights into your studies. Add two to die rolls to study from vis, or two to the Quality of any text you study from. Your current Art score determines the magnitude of the surroundings you require to get the bonus. See the table for some guidelines."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751345,"modifiedTime":1696141995755,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"8MXIzsBCcXUzkXbm","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Priest","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You have been ordained a priest, which means that you can carry out the sacraments of the Mass, Penance, and Extreme Unction. By your words, you can cause the Son of God to manifest in bread and wine. As a priest you come under the protection of canon law, meaning that you cannot be prosecuted by secular authorities. You are accorded considerable respect due to your position, and few people are willing to insult you. You may be a parish priest. If you are, you cannot take the Poor Flaw. Your normal duties involve hearing confession, preaching to your flock, and ministering to their spiritual needs. If you are Wealthy, your parish is rich enough to pay for a curate to do some of the work for you, and you may be a pluralist, holding the benefices of several parishes. Reform-minded churchmen do not approve of pluralism. If you are not a parish priest, the Wealthy Virtue and Poor Flaw affect you normally. You may be employed as a curate to a parish priest, or a chaplain to a wealthy individual, or in any other capacity requiring education. You may purchase Academic Abilities during character generation. You must take the Minor Personality Flaw Vow as one of your normal Flaws, for your vow of celibacy. This Virtue is only available to male characters, and is compatible with the Magister in Artibus Major Virtue. ","source":"ArM5","page":47,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"priest"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751356,"modifiedTime":1696141995761,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"8ajAlNqJ5KxnhdYK","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Guardian Angel","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"guardian-angel","description":"You have learned to hear the words of a divine watcher who gives you practical and spiritual advice. The angel whispers in your ear and tells you what is best for you spiritually, rather than materially. He approves of violence only when there is a holy reason — often difficult to demonstrate. If you act against the angels advice, he may leave you until you correct your ways. The angel has only a limited awareness of your thoughts, but when you speak aloud, he can hear and converse with you. Your guardian angel can also help in two practical ways. First, he can grant you a +5 bonus to Soak. Second, he can grant you a Magic Resistance of 15. This magic resistance is not compatible with a magus’s Parma Magica, or magic resistance from most other sources, but it does add to the magic resistance resulting from Faith Points (see page 189). The angel only grants you these bonuses if you are acting in accordance with Gods will. 43"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751338,"modifiedTime":1696141995770,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jyD9OjMnXTZeke24","_id":"8asRa5jEKfKewF3c","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Faerie Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"faerie-magic","description":"You have been initiated into the Outer Mystery of Faerie Magic (see page 92), and thus are a member of House Merinita. Note that all Merinita magi gain this Virtue for free at character generation."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751220,"modifiedTime":1696141995777,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"8y4OOthAxa00eMC2","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Troupe Upbringing","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":50,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"troupe-upbringing","description":"You were raised among a group of enter tainers, spending much of your childhood traveling from town to town. Rolls involving Abilities in a selected area (which you should have approved by the storyguide) receive a +2 modifier. Examples might include tumbling and acrobatics, knife throwing and juggling, or storytelling and acting."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751216,"modifiedTime":1696141995784,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"9vt8UaeytpS9Sk5m","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Personal Vis Source","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":47,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"personal-vis-source","description":"You have exclusive access to a supply of raw vis. Determine the amount and type with the help of your troupe; the yield should be about one tenth as much as the player covenant expects to gather per year at the beginning of the saga. The yield of your source does not normally change over the course of time, even if the covenant uncovers new sources."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751269,"modifiedTime":1696141995793,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"9xVHRzNknDyxGfWu","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Covenfolk","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You are a member of the covenant staff, and may have lived there all your life. You are supported by the covenant, and so your standard of living is determined by the covenants resources rather than your own. You may not take the Wealthy Major Virtue or the Poor Major Flaw.","source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"free"},"indexKey":"covenfolk"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751276,"modifiedTime":1696141995800,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"CoxB6DSMq2bRMl47","_id":"BC8Q6zheRi3L35x5","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Harnessed Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"harnessed-magic","description":"You have great control over your spells. You are able to cancel any of your spells simply by concentrating. You can even cancel the magic in magic items which you created. The act of canceling your magic should be treated as if you were casting a spell for timing and concentration purposes. If you are distracted and fail a Concentration roll, another attempt may be made in a later round. Spells and magic items can be canceled out over any distance, but once they have been canceled, you must recast a spell or reinvest a power in a magic item to start the effect again. The drawback is that when you die, all of your spells and magic items sputter out."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751291,"modifiedTime":1696141995806,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"CQeDoyInsuC2EyCd","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Improved Characteristics","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"improved-characteristics","description":"You have an additional three points to spend on buying Characteristics, but you are still limited to a maximum score of +3 in any single Characteristic unless you take the Virtue Great Characteristic. You may take this Virtue multiple times."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751323,"modifiedTime":1696141995811,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"CrFCp6sqaxM2LCZP","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Lightning Reflexes","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":45,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lightning-reflexes","description":"You respond to surprises almost instantly. In fact, your reflexes are sometimes so fast that you don’t have a chance to think about how you are going to respond. Whenever you are surprised or startled, roll a stress die + Quickness. If you get a 3 or better, you respond reflexively. You must tell the storyguide on each occasion what one type of action (attacking, blocking, running, etc.) you would like to respond with. If attacking in response, you gain +9 to your Initiative Total. The storyguide is the final arbiter of what happens (though it is always in the best interests of your immediate self-preservation). You only react to threats that you are not fully aware of, so you don’t get a bonus against an assassin you watch sneak up on you. Note that you do not get a choice about whether to react. You could just as easily skewer a friend sneaking up in fun as you would an assassin about to strike. Also note that you must perceive an action to react to it — you can still be easily killed in your sleep. This Virtue gives you no special powers of perception."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751301,"modifiedTime":1696141995818,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"DbP5BbWFReI7WImS","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Flexible Formulaic Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"flexible-formulaic-magic","description":"You can vary the effects of formulaic spells to a slight degree, while still getting the benefits of casting known magic. You may raise or lower the casting level of the spell by five to raise or lower one (only) of Range, Duration, and Target by one step, as long as this does not violate any of the normal limits on formulaic magic. Casting success, fatigue loss, and Penetration are all calculated based on the casting level of the spell. You cannot manipulate Ritual magic in this way."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751234,"modifiedTime":1696141995823,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"ryEkrZYbf9tQGIrO","_id":"DnJY1Mp2Pt8mUrY6","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Animal Ken","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.ERQhqr8T8QSBiSzr","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.skills.animalKen.xpMod","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["xpBonusSupernaturalAbility"],"subtype":["animalKen"],"option":[null]}},"_id":"0CC31dpYw2eJPkRm","transfer":true,"name":"Xp bonus","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"animal-ken","description":"You can communicate with animals as if they were human beings. Choosing this Virtue confers the Ability Animal Ken 1 (page 62)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751287,"modifiedTime":1696141995827,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"ERQhqr8T8QSBiSzr","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Mercenary Captain","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You lead a small company of mercenaries (5 to 10), for hire to the highest bidder. You are much like a knight-errant, only without the prestige. During your travels you have gained great wealth — and squandered it — several times over. You may take Martial Abilities during character generation. If you are Poor, you lead only a couple of other mercenaries, but you and they may have armor and weapons available to normal characters. If you are Wealthy you lead about twenty mercenaries, and can delegate some of the work to sergeants. This Virtue is available to male and female characters.","source":"ArM5","page":46,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"mercenary-captain"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751273,"modifiedTime":1696141995833,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"EmT2qunXJSQ57vIV","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Fast Caster","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"fast-caster","description":"Your magic takes less time to perform than that of other magi. You gain +3 to Initiative to cast spells in combat."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751318,"modifiedTime":1696141995838,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"EnvzceNd8dj0oe0y","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Magic Sensitivity","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Item.FlfjKSCeCKnOqjIa","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.skills.magicSensitivity.bonus","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["bonusSupernaturalAbility"],"subtype":["magicSensitivity"],"option":[null]}},"name":"XP Bonus","icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","_id":"ao3iOjP0tkReTUIC","description":"","transfer":true,"statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":45,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"magic-sensitivity","description":"You are often able to identify a place or object as magical. However, your sensitivity makes you more susceptible to magical effects: subtract your Magic Sensitivity score from all magic resistance rolls you make. Choosing this Virtue confers the Ability Magic Sensitivity 1 (page 66)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751342,"modifiedTime":1696141995842,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"FlfjKSCeCKnOqjIa","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Skilled Parens","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"skilled-parens","description":"Your parens was more powerful, and a better teacher, than is common. You gain an additional 60 experience points and 30 spell levels during apprenticeship. This Virtue has no effect on your study after apprenticeship, but you still have a close relationship with a powerful magus."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751354,"modifiedTime":1696141995847,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"GllC6922LmZGurtr","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Free Expression","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"free-expression","description":"You have the imagination and creativity needed to compose a new ballad or to paint an original picture, and have the potential to be a great artist. You get a +3 bonus on all rolls to create a new work of art."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751328,"modifiedTime":1696141995851,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"GoWxfOYA2B7pBtwl","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Knight","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You are a knight, a member of the noble classes and one of the elite warriors of Europe. Unless you are Poor, you may have high quality weapons and armor, and a horse. Typical armaments for a mid-13th century knight are lance, sword, heater shield, a complete mail suit, and a warhorse. You may take Martial Abilities during character generation. The Wealthy Virtue and Poor Flaw affect you normally. This Virtue is only available to male characters, and is compatible with the Landed Noble Virtue.","source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"knight"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751279,"modifiedTime":1696141995856,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"HhQuNGN1LYiHhOut","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Good Teacher","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.HkspYnZE3BMfKqdB","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"key":"system.bonuses.activities.writing","value":"3","mode":2,"priority":null},{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.activities.teacher","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["activities","activities"],"subtype":["writing","teacher"],"option":[null,null]}},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","_id":"EolKipnLg6rW6AL2","transfer":true,"name":"Good teacher","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"good-teacher","description":"You can explain new concepts and skills with great facility. Add three to the Quality of any books that you write, and five to the Advancement Total of anyone who studies with you."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751320,"modifiedTime":1696141995860,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"HkspYnZE3BMfKqdB","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
