{"name":"Dowsing","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Item.RHaiLnvcarbwKsPh","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.skills.dowsing.bonus","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["bonusSupernaturalAbility"],"subtype":["dowsing"],"option":[null]}},"name":"XP Bonus","icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","_id":"yjNMYB5CqA3yMf2r","description":"","transfer":true,"statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"dowsing","description":"You have the ability to find things nearby through the use of a dowsing rod (usually a forked stick) and your own intuitive sense. Choosing this Virtue confers the Ability Dowsing 1 (page 64)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751253,"modifiedTime":1696141995956,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"RHaiLnvcarbwKsPh","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Strong-willed","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You cannot easily be coerced into activities, beliefs, or feelings. You get +3 on any roll which may require strength of will.","source":"ArM5","page":49,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"strong-willed"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751295,"modifiedTime":1696141995962,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"ROv4KedInHt759Sr","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Magister In Artibus","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You have incepted Master of Arts in one of the universities of Europe (Paris, Bologna, Oxford, Cambridge, Montpellier, Arezzo or Salamanca) and completed your two years’ regency of compulsory teaching. You are entitled to be addressed as Magister, are subject only to canon law, and may teach anywhere in Europe. You are at least (25 – Int) years old, and must have scores of at least 5 in Latin and Artes Liberales. You have, however, spent eight years in a university, and gain an additional 30 experience points in each of those years, for a total of 240 additional experience points over and above your allowance based on age. You may buy Academic Abilities during character generation, and must spend your additional experience points on Academic Abilities or Teaching. You must spend two seasons teaching to maintain yourself and your reputation as a dependable instructor. These two seasons are spread between September and June, so you are genuinely free in the summer. If you take the Poor flaw, you are still genuinely free in the summer. If you take the Wealthy virtue, you can maintain your reputation with a single seasons teaching. This Virtue is only available to male characters, and is compatible with the Hermetic Magus, Mendicant Friar, and Priest Virtues.","source":"ArM5","page":45,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"magister-in-artibus"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751305,"modifiedTime":1696141995966,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"5doiTaY9KQf8IBzO","_id":"RjbpIat6dkHYeCC3","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Failed Apprentice","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You were once apprenticed to a mage, but something kept you from completing your studies. Perhaps your Gift was incomplete or some grievous mishap robbed you of it altogether. You may still work for your former master or for the covenant in some other capacity. Magi welcome you and have compassion for you — those who are given to such emotions, anyway. You may learn Academic and Arcane Abilities during character creation, and you are familiar with the lives of magi. You may not have The Gift, but if your Gift was not completely destroyed, you may have some Supernatural Abilities. You may learn Magic Theory and serve a magus as a laboratory assistant. The Wealthy Virtue and Poor Flaw affect you normally. This Virtue is available to male and female characters.","source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"failed-apprentice"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751231,"modifiedTime":1696141995973,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"Tay3OdWxhtiBUeUC","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Greater Purifying Touch","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"greater-purifying-touch","description":"You can, with a touch and the expenditure of a Fatigue level, cure a single serious disease. This disease should be either life-threatening or seriously disabling, and should be one from which people do not normally recover by themselves. You must choose the disease that you can cure when you take this Virtue, and you can only cure that disease. You can only choose a disease, not other types of injury or misfortune. See page 180 for more information on diseases."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751289,"modifiedTime":1696141995980,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Sym94leLiWXQ3Rh9","_id":"TbUUR8JV6cMb33cy","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Cautious With (ability)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"cautious-with-ability","description":"You are very careful with a specific Ability, and are less likely to fail spectacularly if you do fail when using it. You roll two fewer botch dice than normal whenever you are required to roll botch dice for that Ability. This may mean that you roll no botch dice. This Virtue may apply to any Ability, even one you cannot learn at character creation."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751233,"modifiedTime":1696141995984,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"UIEuTtAQStXlWrlk","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Latent Magic Ability","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"latent-magic-ability","description":"You have a magical quality that has not yet manifested itself. You probably do not realize you have this capacity; if you are a magus, your master failed to detect it during your apprenticeship. At the storyguides discretion, this quality might appear spontaneously or because of some relevant event (like drinking faerie wine). This is not The Gift, and the latent ability is more limited than that. 44"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751307,"modifiedTime":1696141995991,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"UR0gka6nBfI49hk2","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Verditius Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":50,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"verditius-magic","description":"You have been initiated into the Outer Mystery of Verditius Magic (see page 93), and thus are a member of House Verditius. Note that all Verditius magi gain this Virtue for free at character creation."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751303,"modifiedTime":1696141995996,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"UqLHAzXO2F89LGa4","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Clear Thinker","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"clear-thinker","description":"You think logically and rationally. You get a +3 bonus on all rolls to resist lies, confusion, befuddlement, and subterfuge — whether magical or mundane."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751255,"modifiedTime":1696141996001,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"Wb8q9XxJdwwHhGBN","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Merchant","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You live from the buying and selling of goods. You may be a peddler, if you are relatively poor, a shopkeeper, or a traveling merchant. The Wealthy Major Virtue and Poor Major Flaw affect you normally.","source":"ArM5","page":46,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"free"},"indexKey":"merchant"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751251,"modifiedTime":1696141996007,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"CoxB6DSMq2bRMl47","_id":"Wdh5CimLU5kJMAgz","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Heartbeast","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"heartbeast","description":"You have been initiated into the Outer Mystery of the Heartbeast (see page 91), and thus are a member of House Bjornaer. Note that all Bjornaer magi gain this Virtue for free at character creation."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751266,"modifiedTime":1696141996013,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"XStob6gRj9fsPupD","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Piercing Gaze","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":47,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"piercing-gaze","description":"By staring intently at people you make them feel uneasy, as if you are peering into their souls. Those with ulterior motives, uneasy consciences, or lying tongues must make rolls against an appropriate Personality Trait, Guile, or whatever the storyguide deems appropriate, to remain calm. Furthermore, you gain a +3 to rolls involving intimidation. Faeries and demons are unfazed by your power."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751355,"modifiedTime":1696141996017,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"XTGU8VfDOzW1914b","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Puissant (ability)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"J0QJLeqXymMl2eAe","changes":[{"key":"","mode":2,"value":"","priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.gA4tFkUvBXok0DiN","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["none"],"subtype":["none"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Puissant ability to be configured","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"puissant-ability","description":"You are particularly adept with one Ability, and add 2 to its value whenever you use it. Note that you do not, in general, use an Ability when learning it, teaching it, or writing about it. You may only take this Virtue once for a given Ability, but may take it more than once for different Abilities."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751311,"modifiedTime":1696141996022,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"XnuBykikUvpAdghI","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Entrancement","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Item.XrU7t1oCkbk8we6a","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.skills.entrancement.bonus","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["bonusSupernaturalAbility"],"subtype":["entrancement"],"option":[null]}},"name":"XP Bonus","icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","_id":"EOOHBfrsl5vyRKLk","description":"","transfer":true,"statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":42,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"entrancement","description":"You have the power to control anothers will by staring into their eyes and giving them a verbal command. Choosing this Virtue confers the Ability Entrancement 1 (page 65)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751211,"modifiedTime":1696141996026,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Sym94leLiWXQ3Rh9","_id":"XrU7t1oCkbk8we6a","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Student Of (realm)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":49,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"student-of-realm","description":"You have been trained in the mystical aspects of one of the four realms of power (Divine, Faerie, Infernal, or Magic), and you have a +2 bonus on all uses of the appropriate Lore. You may take that Lore at character generation even if you cannot learn other Arcane Abilities. You may take this Virtue multiple times, for a different realm each time. You may not take Student of (Realm) and Puissant Ability for the same Lore. 49"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751274,"modifiedTime":1696141996031,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"Y2ICFnWcIgvMp8JH","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Custos","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You are an employee of a covenant, but you have high status within the walls. You may be a grog, or a specialist, or a manager. You may take one group of restricted Abilities during character generation, either Martial, Academic, or Arcane Abilities. If you choose Martial or Arcane Abilities, you may still learn to speak Latin, although you cannot read or write it. As a covenant employee, your wealth is determined by the covenants prosperity, and you may not take the Wealthy Virtue or Poor Flaw. This Virtue is available to male and female characters. This Virtue may also apply to employees of other institutions, such as a noble household or a monastery.","source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"custos"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751298,"modifiedTime":1696141996035,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"YxE1U2BPpRC78LzH","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Relic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"relic","description":"You own a holy relic, such as the finger bone of a saint, with one Faith point in it. This can be built into any other item you possess (a sword, for instance)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751353,"modifiedTime":1696141996043,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"aUOssKM7kWGX4Yrf","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Wanderer","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"","source":"ArM5","page":50,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"free"},"indexKey":"wanderer"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751314,"modifiedTime":1696141996048,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"CoxB6DSMq2bRMl47","_id":"aaOt84Ro8pnzaTJh","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Mendicant Friar","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/social.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_kuhc1tso94g","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Social Status","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You are a follower of St. Francis or St. Dominic, going among the rich and poor, spreading the word of God and giving comfort to the sick, homeless, hungry, or dying. You are sworn to serve the Church for the rest of your life, but your wandering habits are considered suspect by the local bishop and parish clergy, and you lack political influence within the organization. Like all clerics, however, you are only subject to canon law. Due to your training, you may take Academic Abilities during character generation. If you wish, you may be an ordained priest and may officiate at marriages, baptisms, funerals, and the Mass, though the parish clergy may resent your interfering on their “turf.” You do not need to take the Priest Virtue in addition to this one if you do want to be ordained. You have sworn vows of poverty, chastity, and obedience, which together constitute a Major Story Flaw (Monastic Vows, see page 56) which you must take if you take this Virtue (this Flaw balances other Virtues as normal). You may not take the Wealthy Virtue or Poor Flaw. This Virtue is only available to male characters, and is compatible with the Magister in Artibus Major Virtue.","source":"ArM5","page":46,"type":"social","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"mendicant-friar"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751209,"modifiedTime":1696141996052,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Dlca5muDKIfBSi6F","_id":"aj29upFPrr22gfpC","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Wealthy","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"custom","page":0,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"wealthy","description":"You are a rich member of your class. You may spend three seasons per year on study or adventuring, as you can pay people to look after your interests, and these seasons are genuinely free. Exactly how wealthy you are depends on your social class; a noble would have at least a dozen servants, including some bodyguards, while a wealthy townsman would have a good house and maybe three servants. Whatever your class, you are wealthy enough to afford goods generally associated with a higher class, and thus risk being labeled a vulgar social climber. Wealthy characters may live at a covenant, but they are not supported by the covenant. As all Hermetic magi are supported by their covenant, no magi may take this Virtue."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751284,"modifiedTime":1696141996059,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jyD9OjMnXTZeke24","_id":"amQNvEVoSxbTHQkY","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Cautious Sorcerer","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"cautious-sorcerer","description":"You are very careful with magic, and are less likely to fail spectacularly if you do fail. You roll three fewer botch dice when casting 40 spells (either spontaneous or formulaic), and when working in the laboratory. This Virtue may not reduce the number of botch dice rolled below one. However, its effects are applied before any other effects which reduce botch dice, such as spell mastery (see page 86), and they may reduce the number of botch dice to zero."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751219,"modifiedTime":1696141996064,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"bfQCFMniVB6m9xwZ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Enduring Magic","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"enduring-magic","description":"The effects of your spells tend to last longer than usual (though Concentration, Momentary, and Ring spells remain just that). The storyguide secretly rolls a simple die; the number rolled is a multiple to the spells normal duration. This is usually, but not always, a good thing. This Virtue does not affect the duration of Ritual spells."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751288,"modifiedTime":1696141996068,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"c0a5107EifsKzCvJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Arcane Lore","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":40,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"arcane-lore","description":"You may take Arcane Abilities during character generation. Unless you have The Gift, you cannot learn Parma Magica. You get an additional 50 experience points, which must be spent on Arcane Abilities. A Gifted character who is not a Hermetic magus and knows Parma Magica must take the Major Story Flaw Enemy: Entire Order of Hermes, as magi are bound by their Oath to slay the character on sight, unless he immediately joins the Order. Such a character cannot be played in a normal saga, as the other player characters have to kill him."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751333,"modifiedTime":1696141996074,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"cCLlcN0tP1ckRCSO","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Lesser Purifying Touch","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lesser-purifying-touch","description":"You can, with a touch and the expenditure of a Fatigue level, heal a specific illness. This illness should be one that people often recover from on their own, or one that is not particularly serious. You can only choose an illness, not an injury or other misfortune. See page 180 for rules on diseases."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751231,"modifiedTime":1696141996079,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"cU3ptphkKIdJ29J7","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Social Contacts","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":49,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"social-contacts","description":"You have a broad range of acquaintances in a specific social circle (specified when this Virtue is purchased), accumulated over years of travel and socializing. Almost everywhere you go, you meet someone you know, or can get in touch with someone who can help you. Whenever you are somewhere new, you can contact someone on a simple Presence roll against an Ease Factor of 6. The storyguide may modify this target number upward for very small areas or areas where it is extremely unlikely that you would know someone. You may purchase this Virtue more than once, each time specifying a different social group."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751326,"modifiedTime":1696141996083,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"cajUqfjTHy0FXvdO","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Strong Faerie Blood","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"_id":"ghUg7E1TBNc4nCJZ","changes":[{"key":"system.realms.faeric.aligned","value":"true","mode":5,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.HKnN71E0GJQ7aBP2","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["realm"],"subtype":["faeric"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Fae aligned","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":49,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"strong-faerie-blood","description":"The blood of the fay is strong in you. Perhaps one of your parents was actually a faerie, or maybe you were conceived or born in a place of great faerie power. This ancestry grants you several abilities. First, you have natural longevity. You start making aging rolls at the age of fifty, rather than the normal 35, and get –3 to Aging Rolls, cumulative with any other bonuses. Second, you have faerie eyes. This gives you the Virtue Second Sight (see page 48) at no cost, and you can see normally in darkness or semi-darkness, such as in deep woods or at night. Your eyes look mostly normal, but are an unusual and vivid color. Third, you may learn Faerie Lore during character generation. Finally, you get the benefits of a particular type of fay heritage, as given in the Virtue Faerie Blood (page 42). Your specific fay heritage is clearly visible. Choose one physical quirk, such as small horns, literally blue blood, or eyes without irises and pupils, appropriate to the faeries from which you are descended. You may not have both Faerie Blood and Strong Faerie Blood. This is a Supernatural Virtue, and you cannot lose it when being trained as a magus (see page 106). If your master cannot preserve the ability, you cannot be trained."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751249,"modifiedTime":1696141996089,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"Sym94leLiWXQ3Rh9","_id":"cyufl6WghNbW3tRn","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Light Touch","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":45,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"light-touch","description":"You have especially good hand-eye coordination and great proficiency for using your hands in precise, fast ways. You gain +1 to all rolls involving subtle manipulation of objects (like picking pockets) and roll one less botch die than you normally would in such activities (minimum of one). This bonus does not apply to archery, but does apply to playing musical instruments."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751214,"modifiedTime":1696141996094,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"czOfbf4I6r5VqqVG","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Venus's Blessing","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"","source":"ArM5","page":50,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"venuss-blessing"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751263,"modifiedTime":1696141996098,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"dEQO52knwTj0k0XG","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Inoffensive To Animals (Hermetic)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"Your Gift does not bother animals, although it still has the normal effects on people. Animals with a Might score might react either way, depending on the animal. As a rule, if the animal reacts positively to The Gift most of the time, it reacts positively to you because you do have The Gift. If it reacts negatively, this Virtue over-rides it. UnGifted characters may take this Virtue if they have the Flaw Magical Air (page 56).","source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"inoffensive-to-animals-hermetic"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751257,"modifiedTime":1696141996102,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"eEItQEYvNKRZ6iMQ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Warrior","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":50,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"warrior","description":"You have been trained to fight, and may have spent some time campaigning, perhaps on one of the Crusades. You may acquire Martial Abilities during character creation, and gain an additional 50 experience points which must be spent on Martial Abilities."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751312,"modifiedTime":1696141996107,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"f0bKa372IShdLGWy","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
