{"name":"Large","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[{"_id":"CULCFmHIjMOPXI26","changes":[{"key":"system.vitals.siz.value","value":"1","mode":2,"priority":null}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.GTnrsLNpdMjrMoIl","tint":"#000000","transfer":true,"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["vitals"],"subtype":["size"],"option":[null]}},"name":"Size + 1","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"large","description":"Your Size is +1 instead of 0, so you are between six and seven feet tall. This means that the severity of wounds you take increases in six point intervals rather than five point intervals. (See page 171). You cannot take both this Virtue and Giant Blood, Small Frame, or Dwarf."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751244,"modifiedTime":1696141996287,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"wvw9y5q5PGPcQa27","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Inventive Genius","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"inventive-genius","description":"Invention comes naturally to you. You receive +3 on Lab Totals when you invent new spells, craft magic items, and make potions. If you experiment, you get +6."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751271,"modifiedTime":1696141996294,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"C8jqPqfblXk6hGCE","_id":"wwIJH1db3HEr2qfU","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Intuition","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"intuition","description":"You have a natural sensitivity that allows you to make the right decisions more often than luck can account for. Whenever you are given a choice in which luck plays a major role (such as deciding which of three unexplored paths to follow), you have a good chance of choosing correctly. The storyguide should secretly roll a simple die. On a 6+, your intuition kicks in and you make whatever might be considered the “right” decision. Otherwise, you fail to get any flash of insight and must make the decision without aid."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751319,"modifiedTime":1696141996299,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"xjleRySifX2v6ech","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Sense Holiness And Unholiness","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","origin":"Compendium.arm5e.virtues.xmmX6YHUvCRrCTXk","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.skills.senseHolyAndUnholy.xpMod","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["xpBonusSupernaturalAbility"],"subtype":["senseHolyAndUnholy"],"option":[null]}},"_id":"sVVqC4kTsL81H1hn","transfer":true,"name":"xp bonus","description":"","statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"sense-holiness-and-unholiness","description":"You are able to feel the presence of good and evil. In auras of particularly strong divine or infernal influence, your sensitivity may overwhelm you. Choosing this Virtue confers the Ability Sense Holiness and Unholiness 1 (page 67)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751238,"modifiedTime":1696141996304,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"xmmX6YHUvCRrCTXk","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Enchanting Music","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[{"origin":"Item.xqdb4Sgg7sDrcIMG","duration":{"startTime":null,"seconds":null,"combat":null,"rounds":null,"turns":null,"startRound":null,"startTurn":null},"disabled":false,"tint":"#000000","changes":[{"mode":2,"key":"system.bonuses.skills.enchantingMusic.bonus","value":"5","priority":null}],"flags":{"arm5e":{"type":["bonusSupernaturalAbility"],"subtype":["enchantingMusic"],"option":[null]}},"name":"XP Bonus","icon":"icons/svg/aura.svg","_id":"9cOfrDS6Vq8HtBzE","description":"","transfer":true,"statuses":[]}],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":41,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"enchanting-music","description":"When you set your mind to it, you can magically induce emotions and beliefs in others with your music. Choosing this Virtue confers the Ability Enchanting Music 1 (page 65)."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751293,"modifiedTime":1696141996309,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"xqdb4Sgg7sDrcIMG","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Reserves Of Strength","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"reserves-of-strength","description":"Once per day, when in need, you can perform an incredible feat of strength. For the duration of the action, add +3 to your effective Strength score. Afterwards, though, you must make two Fatigue rolls."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751240,"modifiedTime":1696141996314,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"yCYEbWVF6iKHGICi","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Inoffensive To Animals (General)","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"Your Gift does not bother animals, although it still has the normal effects on people. Animals with a Might score might react either way, depending on the animal. As a rule, if the animal reacts positively to The Gift most of the time, it reacts positively to you because you do have The Gift. If it reacts negatively, this Virtue over-rides it. UnGifted characters may take this Virtue if they have the Flaw Magical Air (page 56).","source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"inoffensive-to-animals-general"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751277,"modifiedTime":1696141996318,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"yDYYzEFv8O3IaXey","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Self-confident","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"description":"You have firm confidence in your own abilities, and have a Confidence Score of two. You also start with five Confidence Points, rather than the usual three. (See page 19 for Confidence rules.)","source":"ArM5","page":48,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"self-confident"},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751335,"modifiedTime":1696141996324,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jegZHVtv21smauPD","_id":"zIdsubgVSir0JHsr","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Ghostly Warder","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/generalVirtue.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_qajjxhee95m","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/General","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":43,"type":"general","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"ghostly-warder","description":"A ghost watches over you. It might be a grandparent, a childhood friend, or anyone else who cares for you enough to stay around after death. The ghost is invisible and silent to all but you and those with Second Sight (see page 67). It can see and hear what is going on around you and makes an excellent spy, since it can leave your presence once per day for up to half an hour. However, death does not leave people in their normal state of mind, so the ghost probably has some quirks that make it less than dependable — it might even encourage you to join it on the other side. The ghost has 300 experience points in various Abilities that it can use to advise you, and ghosts may take any Abilities. See page 194 for an example of a ghostly warder."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751304,"modifiedTime":1696141996328,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"jyD9OjMnXTZeke24","_id":"zhTC8p1Sl6DfaXvJ","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Lesser Immunity","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/supernatural.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nh7mgwj6rq","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Supernatural","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":44,"type":"supernatural","impact":{"value":"minor"},"indexKey":"lesser-immunity","description":"You are immune to some hazard which is either rare, or not deadly, or both. See “Greater Immunity,” page 43."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751265,"modifiedTime":1696141996333,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"XwOh5akgyjxNE2dG","_id":"zj8E4f2T4xrUzoqb","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
{"name":"Mythic Blood","type":"virtue","img":"systems/arm5e/assets/icons/VF/hermetic.svg","effects":[],"flags":{"core":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_nxctmjlqqdb","path":"Virtues#/CF_SEP/Hermetic","color":"#000000"}},"system":{"source":"ArM5","page":47,"type":"hermetic","impact":{"value":"major"},"indexKey":"mythic-blood","description":"You are a blood descendant of either a wizard of legend (possibly one of the Twelve Founders, or some other ancient and powerful sorcerer) or a supernatural being (such as a dragon). Your potent Gift means that you do not lose Fatigue levels if your Casting Total falls short of the level of a formulaic spell by less than ten points, although you do lose Fatigue if the spell fails completely. You must expend Fatigue normally to cast spontaneous magic, and if you fail to cast a formulaic spell you lose the normal number of Fatigue levels. Additionally, you may choose one special magic feat which you can invoke at will and cancel at will, as often as you like. Invoking this feat takes as long as fast-casting a mastered formulaic spell (see page 87), and requires the same level of concentration. The effect should be designed as a Hermetic effect, with a level + Penetration limited as below. The Penetration of the effect is not modified by the magus’s Penetration Ability score, and cannot be negative, so that the highest possible level of the effect is 30. Invocation: Level + Penetration Speak and Gesture: 30 Speak: 25 Gesture: 20 Nither Speak nor Gesture: 15 This Virtue includes a Minor Magical Focus in an area related to your legendary ancestor and a hereditary Minor Personality Flaw (both at no extra cost). Mythic Blood is not particularly uncommon in the Order of Hermes, so this Virtue does not grant any Reputation."},"_stats":{"systemId":"arm5e","systemVersion":"2.2.2.15","coreVersion":"11.311","createdTime":1662235751274,"modifiedTime":1696141996339,"lastModifiedBy":"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru"},"folder":"ryEkrZYbf9tQGIrO","_id":"zr4WbJ6fSNAp3922","sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"1JBSgWiiwizu7vru":3}}
